<feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><title>LightQuanta</title><link href="http://sanghan.me/" rel="alternate"></link><link href="http://sanghan.me/feeds/posts.atom.xml" rel="self"></link><id>http://sanghan.me/</id><updated>2015-03-20T00:00:00-07:00</updated><entry><title>Everythingâ€™s An Object, So What? slug: object_orientedÂ date:</title><link href="http://sanghan.me/blog/2015/03/everythings-an-object-so-what-slug-object_oriented-date/" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-03-20T00:00:00-07:00</updated><author><name>Sang Han</name></author><id>tag:sanghan.me,2015-03-20:blog/2015/03/everythings-an-object-so-what-slug-object_oriented-date/</id><summary type="html">&lt;div class="figure"&gt;
&lt;img alt="comic" src="{filename}img/languaes.png" /&gt;
&lt;p class="caption"&gt;comic&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A look into Python&amp;#8217;s Data Model, what it means to be object&amp;nbsp;oriented.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class="simple"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Normal&amp;nbsp;Methods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Class&amp;nbsp;Methods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Static&amp;nbsp;Methods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Defining a method usually look like&amp;nbsp;this&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span id="line-1"&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nc"&gt;Pokemon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-2"&gt;    &lt;span class="sd"&gt;&amp;quot;&amp;quot;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-3"&gt;&lt;span class="sd"&gt;    A contrived Pokemon DataModel&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-4"&gt;&lt;span class="sd"&gt;    &amp;quot;&amp;quot;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-5"&gt;    &lt;span class="c"&gt;# Class Attributes owned by the Class&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-6"&gt;    &lt;span class="n"&gt;types&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;fire&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;grass&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;rock&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;electric&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;water&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-7"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-8"&gt;    &lt;span class="k"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nf"&gt;__init__&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nb"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;level&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-9"&gt;        &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;quot;Instantiate a pokemon with a name, type and level.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-10"&gt;        &lt;span class="bp"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-11"&gt;        &lt;span class="k"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nb"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="ow"&gt;not&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="ow"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;types&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-12"&gt;            &lt;span class="k"&gt;raise&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="ne"&gt;AttributeError&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;Pokemon not a valid type&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-13"&gt;        &lt;span class="bp"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nb"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-14"&gt;        &lt;span class="bp"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;level&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;level&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-15"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-16"&gt;    &lt;span class="c"&gt;# Normal Method&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-17"&gt;    &lt;span class="k"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nf"&gt;level_up&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;levels&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mi"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-18"&gt;        &lt;span class="bp"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;level&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;+=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;levels&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-19"&gt;        &lt;span class="k"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;level&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="there-are-three-ways-of-using-methods-from-a-class"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;There are three ways of using methods from a&amp;nbsp;class:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="normal-methods-bound-to-class-instances"&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;1. Normal Methods Bound to Class&amp;nbsp;Instances&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is the typical way of calling&amp;nbsp;methods&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let&amp;#8217;s construct instances of Pokemon and and modify it&amp;#8217;s attributes
using a normal method&amp;nbsp;call.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span id="line-1"&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;pikachu&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Pokemon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;pikachu&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;electric&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-2"&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;onyx&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Pokemon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;onyx&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;12&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;rock&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-3"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-4"&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;# Mutates the instance self.level attribute.&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-5"&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;pikachu&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;level_up&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-6"&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;pikachu&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;level&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-7"&gt;&lt;span class="mi"&gt;6&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;level_up()&lt;/tt&gt; is a normal method because it requires access to the
instances &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;level&lt;/tt&gt; attribute&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="make-the-method-a-class-method"&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;2. Make the method a &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://docs.python.org/2/library/functions.html#classmethod"&gt;class&amp;nbsp;method&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This lets you use attributes of the class without requiring an&amp;nbsp;instance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let&amp;#8217;s inspect our &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;Pokemon&lt;/tt&gt; Class&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span id="line-1"&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;# Class Attribute&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-2"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-3"&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nc"&gt;Pokemon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-4"&gt;    &lt;span class="o"&gt;...&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-5"&gt;    &lt;span class="o"&gt;...&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-6"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-7"&gt;    &lt;span class="nd"&gt;@classmethod&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-8"&gt;    &lt;span class="k"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nf"&gt;weakness&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;cls&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;pokemon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-9"&gt;        &lt;span class="k"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;cls&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;types&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;cls&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;types&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;index&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;pokemon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-10"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-11"&gt;    &lt;span class="nd"&gt;@classmethod&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-12"&gt;    &lt;span class="k"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nf"&gt;effectiveness&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;cls&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;pokemon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-13"&gt;        &lt;span class="k"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;cls&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;types&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;cls&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;index&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;pokemon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-14"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-15"&gt;    &lt;span class="nd"&gt;@staticmethod&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-16"&gt;    &lt;span class="k"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nf"&gt;battle&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;trainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;opponent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-17"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-18"&gt;        &lt;span class="k"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;trainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;!=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;trainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;get_effective&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;opponent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="ow"&gt;and&lt;/span&gt; \
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-19"&gt;           &lt;span class="n"&gt;trainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;!=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;trainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;get_weakness&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;opponent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-20"&gt;            &lt;span class="n"&gt;chances&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;trainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;level&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-21"&gt;        &lt;span class="k"&gt;elif&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;trainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;trainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;get_effective&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;opponent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-22"&gt;            &lt;span class="n"&gt;chances&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;trainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;level&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-23"&gt;        &lt;span class="k"&gt;elif&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;trainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;trainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;get_weakness&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;opponent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-24"&gt;            &lt;span class="n"&gt;chances&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;trainer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;level&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-25"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-26"&gt;        &lt;span class="k"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;trainer&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;chances&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;opponent&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;opponent&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-27"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-28"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-29"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-30"&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Pokemon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;types&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-31"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;fire&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;grass&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;rock&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;electric&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;water&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-32"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-33"&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;# Instance has access to Class attributes&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-34"&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;pikachu&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;types&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-35"&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;fire&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;grass&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;rock&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;electric&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;water&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;Pokemon.types&lt;/tt&gt; is a class level variable, which means it&amp;#8217;s bound to
the class itself. &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;pikachu.types&lt;/tt&gt; is referencing it&amp;#8217;s parent
&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;Pokemon.types&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="a-note-on-classmethods"&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Note on&amp;nbsp;Classmethods:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
The class method can &lt;span class="caps"&gt;ONLY&lt;/span&gt; access data that every instance of the
class has access to. This typically means that it can see the
methods belonging to the class, and any variables defined outside of
those methods, for example:&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;pikachu.type&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;strong&gt;(singular type, not types)&lt;/strong&gt; is a variable which
belongs only to instances of the &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;Pokemon&lt;/tt&gt; class and can only be used
when you construct an object of that&amp;nbsp;class.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Trying to access &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;type&lt;/tt&gt; from it&amp;#8217;s class raises an &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;AttributeError&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span id="line-1"&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Pokemon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-2"&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;---------------------------------------------------------------------------&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-3"&gt;&lt;span class="ne"&gt;AttributeError&lt;/span&gt;                            &lt;span class="n"&gt;Traceback&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;most&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;recent&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;call&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;last&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-4"&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;python&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;input&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mi"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;fff28c0ed2a2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="ow"&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;module&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-5"&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;----&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Pokemon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-6"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-7"&gt;&lt;span class="ne"&gt;AttributeError&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nb"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nb"&gt;object&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;Pokemon&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;has&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;no&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;attribute&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;type&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="a-class-method-is-oftentimes-useful-for-writing-methods-which-are-generalized-for-a-whole-class-to-be-applied-on-instances"&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&amp;gt; A class method is oftentimes useful for writing methods which are generalized for a whole class to be applied on&amp;nbsp;instances.&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span id="line-1"&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;# Pikachu is Effective Against&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-2"&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Pokemon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;get_effective&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;pikachu&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-3"&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;water&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-4"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-5"&gt;&lt;span class="c"&gt;# Pikachu is Weak Against&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-6"&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;Pokemon&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;get_weakness&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;pikachu&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-7"&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;rock&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="make-the-method-a-static-method-and-call-it-as-class-instance-method-or-classname-method"&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;3. Make the method a &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://docs.python.org/2/library/functions.html#staticmethod"&gt;static method&lt;/a&gt; and call it as &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;class_instance.method()&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;ClassName.method()&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Static methods are methods bound to a class which cannot access the
state or properties of the class. This means they can&amp;#8217;t use any
variables belonging to the&amp;nbsp;class.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A class method is not a static method and a static method is not a class
method because the &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;cls&lt;/tt&gt; argument behaves a lot like &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;self&lt;/tt&gt; in a
normal method. That is &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;cls&lt;/tt&gt; is automatically assigned a value of
&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;ClassType&lt;/tt&gt;. If you didn&amp;#8217;t specify it with the &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;cls&lt;/tt&gt; input then the
first argument would be assigned the value of &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;ClassType&lt;/tt&gt; (as if it
were &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;cls&lt;/tt&gt;, since its just the conventional name) and all of the other
arguments would be shifted&amp;nbsp;over.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The static method isn&amp;#8217;t like this. Static methods don&amp;#8217;t have a
predefined argument. Static methods can only use variables which were
given as arguments or defined inside of the&amp;nbsp;function.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For a high level explanation you can think of classes as being a generic
object and methods as just regular&amp;nbsp;functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you define a method of a class (in the normal way) and instantiate
the class into an object, the methods are bound when the object is
created and with the first argument being given the object the method
belongs to. The regular method is there only when the class is
instantiated into an&amp;nbsp;object&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you define a class method the function the method is bound to the
class, not an object. So it is bound when the class is defined. That
means a classmethod is there as soon as the class is defined and stays
there for all instances of the&amp;nbsp;class&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A static method is similar to the class method; it&amp;#8217;s there as soon as
the object is defined, however it doesn&amp;#8217;t have any preset values bound
to any of its&amp;nbsp;arguments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Each one has its merits and uses but it&amp;#8217;s important to use the most
appropriate&amp;nbsp;one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="rule-of-thumb"&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Rule of&amp;nbsp;Thumb&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Doesn&amp;#8217;t require knowing anything about the class or self.
&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;staticmethod&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Doesn&amp;#8217;t require knowing anything about self, but references the class
&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;classmethod&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Needs needs to know about a particular instance of the class, then just
create it like a normal method with &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;self&lt;/tt&gt; but no&amp;nbsp;decorators.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr class="docutils" /&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span id="line-1"&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nc"&gt;foo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;object&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-2"&gt;    &lt;span class="n"&gt;bar&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="bp"&gt;True&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-3"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-4"&gt;    &lt;span class="k"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nf"&gt;__init__&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;baz&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-5"&gt;       &lt;span class="bp"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;baz&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;baz&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-6"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-7"&gt;    &lt;span class="nd"&gt;@classmethod&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-8"&gt;    &lt;span class="k"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nf"&gt;foo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;cls&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-9"&gt;        &lt;span class="k"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;cls&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;bar&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c"&gt;# Returns bar&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-10"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-11"&gt;    &lt;span class="nd"&gt;@classmethod&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-12"&gt;    &lt;span class="k"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nf"&gt;fuz&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;cls&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-13"&gt;        &lt;span class="k"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;cls&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;baz&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="c"&gt;# Error!&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="a-static-method-is-not-a-bound-method"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;A static method is not a bound&amp;nbsp;method&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A static method is not a bound&amp;nbsp;method.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I need to clarify a few definitions because I&amp;#8217;ve used the term bound
rather loosely to mean that it lives in the object namespace, which
isn&amp;#8217;t technically correct when referring to&amp;nbsp;methods.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class="reference external" href="https://docs.python.org/3/howto/descriptor.html#static-methods-and-class-methods"&gt;From a high level perspective this link is
great&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;m going to go into a very low-level overview of what is going on (to
the best of my ability, if I&amp;#8217;m wrong anywhere I&amp;#8217;d love to be&amp;nbsp;corrected).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here are the important&amp;nbsp;points:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class="simple"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Everything in Python is an&amp;nbsp;object&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Every object has a type, identity, and&amp;nbsp;value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The type of an object is itself a
&lt;a class="reference external" href="https://docs.python.org/3/library/stdtypes.html#bltin-type-objects"&gt;type&lt;/a&gt;
and an&amp;nbsp;object.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Functions are objects of &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;`Callable&lt;/tt&gt;
type &amp;lt;&lt;a class="reference external" href="https://docs.python.org/3/reference/datamodel.html#objects-values-and-types"&gt;https://docs.python.org/3/reference/datamodel.html#objects-values-and-types&lt;/a&gt;&amp;gt;`__.
Classes are also callable and usually return an instance of
themselves. Class instances are objects of type &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;ClassName&lt;/tt&gt; only
callable if the &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;__call__&lt;/tt&gt; method is&amp;nbsp;defined.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Classes are actually interpreted as instances of type &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;type&lt;/tt&gt;, so
defining a class is actually an creating an &lt;em&gt;instance&lt;/em&gt; of
&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;`type&lt;/tt&gt; &amp;lt;&lt;a class="reference external" href="https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#type"&gt;https://docs.python.org/3/library/functions.html#type&lt;/a&gt;&amp;gt;`__.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The following are&amp;nbsp;equivalent:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span id="line-1"&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nc"&gt;X&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-2"&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;...&lt;/span&gt;     &lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="mi"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-3"&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;...&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-4"&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;X&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nb"&gt;type&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s"&gt;&amp;#39;X&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;object&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,),&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nb"&gt;dict&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="mi"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;))&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When Python &amp;#8216;executes&amp;#8217; the class definition it takes everything inside
the class definition namespace and uses it for the &amp;#8216;namespace&amp;#8217;
dictionary of the&amp;nbsp;type.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class="simple"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Binding (formally) refers to the process of joining a name to a block
(a module, function body, or class&amp;nbsp;definition).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An instance method is a Callable object which combines a class, a
class instance, and a function/callable. An instance method is said
to be bound if its &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;__self__&lt;/tt&gt; has been set to a class instance and
its &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;__func__&lt;/tt&gt; property has been set to point to the original
function. When the method is called the callable is really returning
&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;f.__func__(f.__self__, &lt;span class="pre"&gt;...)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calling a method, &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;foo&lt;/tt&gt;, on an object x of class X is really doing
this: &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;X.foo(x, &lt;span class="pre"&gt;...)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;. Since foo has been bound (when the class was
instantiated) to the object x of type&amp;nbsp;X.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For class methods the decorator changes &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;__self__&lt;/tt&gt; from pointing to
an instance to pointing to the class itself, so calling
&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;x.foo(...)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;X.foo(...)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt; is really doing &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;X.foo(X, &lt;span class="pre"&gt;...)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;.
This is done when the class is instantiated (as an instance of&amp;nbsp;type).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For static method &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;foo&lt;/tt&gt; the decorator prevents the binding of
&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;__self__&lt;/tt&gt;. So a static method is bound to the module namespace and
the &amp;#64;staticmethod decorator is a
&lt;a class="reference external" href="https://docs.python.org/3/reference/datamodel.html#implementing-descriptors"&gt;descriptor&lt;/a&gt;
which makes the function a &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://docs.python.org/3/reference/datamodel.html#invoking-descriptors"&gt;Direct
Callable&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;#8217;s some sample code which might help demonstrate what I&amp;nbsp;mean:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span id="line-1"&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nc"&gt;A&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;object&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-2"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-3"&gt;    &lt;span class="nd"&gt;@classmethod&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-4"&gt;    &lt;span class="k"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nf"&gt;class_method&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;cls&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;args&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-5"&gt;        &lt;span class="k"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;args&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-6"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-7"&gt;    &lt;span class="nd"&gt;@staticmethod&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-8"&gt;    &lt;span class="k"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nf"&gt;static_method&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;args&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-9"&gt;        &lt;span class="k"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;args&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-10"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-11"&gt;    &lt;span class="k"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nf"&gt;method&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="bp"&gt;self&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;args&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-12"&gt;        &lt;span class="k"&gt;print&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;args&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table border="1" class="docutils"&gt;
&lt;colgroup&gt;
&lt;col width="10%" /&gt;
&lt;col width="29%" /&gt;
&lt;col width="61%" /&gt;
&lt;/colgroup&gt;
&lt;thead valign="bottom"&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th class="head"&gt;Command&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th class="head"&gt;Output&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th class="head"&gt;Notes&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/thead&gt;
&lt;tbody valign="top"&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;type(A)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;type&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;type(A())&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;__main__.A&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;type(A())()&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&amp;lt;__main__.A at 0x112c22a10&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Creates an instance of class A&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;A().class_method&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&amp;lt;bound method type.class_method of &amp;lt;class &lt;span class="pre"&gt;'__main__.A'&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;A().static_method&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&amp;lt;function __main__.static_method&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Belongs to global namespace&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;A().method&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&amp;lt;bound method A.method of &amp;lt;__main__.A object at 0x112bfc8d0&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;A.class_method&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&amp;lt;bound method type.class_method of &amp;lt;class &lt;span class="pre"&gt;'__main__.A'&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;same as before&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;A.static_method&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&amp;lt;function __main__.static_method&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Belongs to global namespace&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;A.method&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;&amp;lt;unbound method A.method&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td&gt;Not bound to an instance yet, but has been bound to a class. Calling A.method(A()) works, but only with input of type A or subclassing A.&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can also add a method to a class like&amp;nbsp;this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span id="line-1"&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nf"&gt;bar&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;obj&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;args&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;):&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-2"&gt;    &lt;span class="k"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;obj&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;__name__&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-3"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;A&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;foo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nb"&gt;classmethod&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;bar&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-4"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;A&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;bar&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;bar&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span id="line-5"&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;A&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;baz&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="nb"&gt;staticmethod&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;baz&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;A.foo&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;A.bar&lt;/tt&gt;, and &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;A.baz&lt;/tt&gt; will behave exactly like the
respective methods, which is sometimes useful if you want to use things
like partial function application or decorators inside of classes. If
you bind a function to an instance, say &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;a=A()&lt;/tt&gt;, then it will behave
like a regular function in the namespace of &lt;tt class="docutils literal"&gt;a&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
